I’m beyond delighted to share with you this incredible day that was just featured by @theodoremagazine 
——
people always ask me “do you approach gay weddings the same straight ones?” honestly, I don’t change much. My job is to document the love between two people. Whoever they love doesn’t really impact how I am able to capture real moments during the day. I think we as photographers get caught up on trying to force those perfect moments, and don’t realize the perfect moments happen on their own.
——
I think one of the most powerful attributes a photographer can have as the ability to observe. The moment you take yourself out of the equation & focus on moments as they organically happen, the moment your work begins to shift into something truly beautiful. 
——
@jack_bartelt_ + @bradley_bartelt thank you for letting me into your space to showcase how beautiful your love is.
——

sometimes your wedding day doesn’t go as planned. this is why it is super important to hire vendors who can improvise last minute so you don’t have to stress.
——
e+j’s original plan was to have their ceremony outside to be able to incorporate their insane venue with utah’s natural beauty. unfortunately, mother nature has other plans. 30 minutes before their ceremony started, torrential rain began to fall which forced the ceremony to be moved inside. 
——
@brittwarnickdesigns & her team, along with everyone in attendance, myself included moved mountains to be able to move everything inside. for this exact reason, i will not be accepting any weddings over 25 people unless a wedding planner and or day of coordinator is present. i have found in instances where i am documenting a wedding without one, i turn into the wedding planner and I’m supposed to know everything that’s happening, which takes away time for me to do my job. 
——
long story short, HIRE A WEDDING PLANNER!!! there is no way we would have been able to execute the beautiful outcome we did if e+j didn’t hire a wedding planner. 

i hope you can feel the day through these just as much as I can! Don’t worry, will be sharing more about the day soon!
——

2nd shooter - @christieqphotography

hello friends, I’m back!
——
I’m sure you didn’t even notice but I have  not shared any work here in quite sometime. I posted a story a couple days ago how this year has been… off. I just wanted to say thank you for every single message I got about changing my policy that I will only shooting weddings if there is a wedding planner / day of coordinator present. 
——
Reading back to what I said, I want to elaborate. My post wasn’t intended to cause contention, but to help understand that photographers simply cannot do everything to insure you have a seamless wedding. I just want to be able to provide the best experience possible. I am a story teller, not a planner or coordinator. 
——
my reasoning behind this decision is for one reason only, client experience. I have noticed when there is not someone organizing the day, that responsibility falls onto me. I solely want to insure I am fully present with my couple so I don’t miss these fleeting moments our beloved couples hired us to capture. The more I am responsible for, the more time it takes away from me doing the job I was hired to do.
——
as you can see, I’m not doing this out of selfishness or because “I’m a big deal” (I’m not, I just am a guy who loves weddings) I just want to remember why I fell in love with wedding photography in the first place. 
——
I  have felt myself slowly felt myself fall out love with my job & I finally realized it’s because I’m spreading myself too thin on wedding days. I can promise you hiring a good planner who knows how to seamlessly execute a wedding event will completely help you to focus on thee most important thing when it comes to your wedding, and that is for you to enjoy stress free!
——
I love this job more than anything. I don’t see myself stopping any time soon, but I know I will if I don’t make this change. Hope you all can understand where I’m coming from. It really takes a whole village to execute all these incredible weddings you are seeing. When selecting your vendors, DO YOU RESEARCH!! Do they have good reviews? Are they communicating with you? Do they understand your vision? Do you connect with them? Weddings are not cheap. Don’t cheap out on your vendors!

A Swiss love story 🇨🇭
——
back in August I have the opportunity to document this incredible wedding in Switzerland, a place I’ve been wanting to visit for quite some time.
——
G is from America, S is from Switzerland. G moved to Switzerland & randomly bumped into S on the train. Now they are happily married. Life is funny like that. With their loved ones, they celebrated in a way I haven’t experienced yet. I’m always so inspired by each of my couples & how different each wedding is.
——
Switzerland is such a magical place and I was so inspired by it all. Already looking forward to the next time I’m there.

NYBFW EDIT l

so excited to finally start rolling out some content from @nybfw especially with the launch of one of my favorite collections that was presented the @saintbridal NEW REALM COLLECTION! this collection feels fresh, new, & innovative. i had to wait until launch day to share these, and couldn’t wait any longer!
——
what i am loving to see throughout this season in bridal fashion is: structural elements, corsets, & separates. when you’re investing in something like what you will be wearing on your wedding day, finding attire that has multi purpose is becoming my new favorite trend. I am so inspired by this collection.
——
congratulations to the saint couture team on this beautiful collection. i hope you all fall in love with these as much as i have.

2023 RECAP
——
As 2023 comes to a close, I just wanted to say thank you to all my clients for the incredible year it has been. You make my job feel more fulfilling than anyone else could. You all inspire me more than I can express.
——
Sharing my top 9 to reflect back on the year & all that comes to mind is gratitude. May your last few days of 2023 be filled with love and happiness! 2024 can’t wait to meet ya.

2024 is here which means new love stories to share!
——
A couple months back I had the opportunity to fly to Nashville to shoot these two in preparation of their wedding day!  it was my first time in the Midwest, and it did not disappoint. Rolling and fast open spaces inspired me beyond compare. There’s just something about knowing you are completely alone, not worrying about other people, solely focused on capturing your couples story. Beyond excited to also be shooting @haegantynes_ & @abram.engle wedding day!
——
I realized as I’m posting these, I only had a handful of sessions last year and wanting to change that this year!  if you want your love documented by me, please visit my website & fill out an inquiry form!
